{
  "texts": [
    "Nan et al (2019) use Wasserstein AutoEncoder (WAE) to model topics, which minimizes the Wasserstein distance between generated documents and input documents.",
    "Rezaee and Ferraro (2020) propose a NTM without using the reparameterization trick.",
    "They generate discrete topic assignments from RNN inspired by Dieng et al (2017).",
    "Wu et al (2021) focus on discovering latent topics from long-tailed corpora.",
    "They propose a causal inference framework to analyze how the long-tailed bias influences topic modeling."
  ]
}